-- Santander Among 15 Banks Lowered by S&P After Spain Downgraded
-- B y   P a t r i c k   C l a r k
-- 2012-02-13T19:15:11Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-13/santander-is-among-15-banks-cut-by-s-p-following-spain-s-credit-downgrade.html
Banco Santander SA (SAN)  and  Banco Bilbao
Vizcaya Argentaria SA (BBVA)  were among 15 Spain-based financial firms
downgraded by Standard & Poor’s, after the
credit-ratings company reduced the nation’s grade last month.  Santander, Spain’s biggest bank, was lowered to A+ from
AA-, while BBVA was reduced to A from A+, S&P said today in a
statement. Both have a negative outlook, S&P said. The ratings
company had cut the grade on Spain’s long-term debt to A from
AA- on Jan. 13.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Patrick Clark in New York at 
